quoteFirst: ‘Gabriel had, just before Shields entered the drawing-room for me, given two violent cries, and had a convulsive fit, very sharp and distorting the face, followed by collapse.  All this passed without my personal cognizance.  He died
quoteLast: ; the others—Watts, mother, Christina, and nurse, in room; Caine and Shields in and out; Watts at Gabriel’s right side, partly supporting him.’
title: Theodore Watts-Dunton: Poet, Novelist, Critic
author: Douglas, James, 1867-1940
